column5: Went out with my father in law for some backcountry bronzebacks north of the sault.  Around 11 am we parked the truck and hiked to our destination.  Fishing was slooooooowwwwwwwwww...  Smallie hits were barely detectable, often it was just a sudden dead weight.  Most fish taken on white twister tails slowly dragged along the bottom while drifting, a new pattern for this lake.   All in all we boated about about 10 including my new PB smallie.  Just over 22.5" and just about as girthy...lol...
Wow, congrads! Looks like a big old warred out old fish lol.    Thanks for sharing, MTBF
Attaboy Dr. Salvelinus What a beauty.... that's a real dark colored bass!!!   Must of give you a good fight Thanks for sharing Leechman
That's a beast of a northern smallie! Congrats!
yaaa good going! same lake we talked about without a name again?
that fish is so old and so big it has "perm-a-tan" to get that dark.  Good on ya!
